<p>A key strategy in making any career transition is identifying and filling gaps in your technical knowledge and experience. As a mechanical engineer transitioning to more software-oriented work, one of these gaps is my lack of collaborative experience on software projects. This post outlines some of the work I’ve contributed to <a href="https://github.com/samuelselleck/holographit" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">holographit</a>, a tool for generating real-life holograms from 3D models, with three other colleagues from my batch at <a href="https://www.recurse.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">the Recurse Center</a></p>

